How to install Jenkins in redhat like (aws amazon ec2):
=======================================================
step-1:

add Jenkins repo to your yum repository
=======================================
sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo

step-2:

important a key file from jenkins-CI to enable installation from the package
============================================================================
sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key

step-3:

update all packages
===================
sudo yum upgrade

step-4:

you have set a jenkin server then java(jdk) is important in your system
=======================================================================
sudo yum install fontconfig java-21-openjdk  --> if this command in case not work then use 

sudo dnf install java-21-amazon-corretto-devel  --> this command also used 

after java installation complete
================================
java -version --> is used to check java version download or not.

step-5:

then install Jenkins
====================
sudo yum install jenkins

step-6:

to enable Jenkins steps by step use below commands
==================================================
1.sudo systemctl daemon-reload
2.sudo systemctl enable jenkins
3.sudo systemctl start jenkins
4.sudo systemctl status jenkins

step-7

go to your aws console then copy your ec2 public ip then paste ur browser
=========================================================================
 13.127.30.171:8080

:8080 is a default port on jenkin server so u must add in ur ip.

step-8

after complete, jenkins server on and showing Adminpassword
===========================================================
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword -->write in ur Linux machine and showing pwd.



















